materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"6jsjr","text":"- benchtop centrifuge with cooling function","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7h2gp","text":"- waterbath sonicator","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dh6c5","text":"- regular lab equipment (pipetts, tips, tubes)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aofbn","text":"- nylon flocked swabs (like FLOQBrush®; CopanItalia Spa)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":37,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"29sd0","text":"- 1μl plastic inoculation loops, disposable, sterile","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8qqv0","text":"- NaCl 0.9% (w/v) aqeous solution","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"evds6","text":"- PBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We are still developing and optimizing this protocol

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"99o96","text":"Two olfactory mucosa samples are collected per person, one nasal swabbing from each nostril.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b44dc","text":"A sterile, disposable swab is inserted in the nasal cavity, (similar to a covid test but more towards the top) to reach the olfactory and not the epithelial mucosa. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"q39t","text":"The swab is gently rolled on the mucosal surface, removed, and the tip is cut and placed in a 15-ml conical centrifuge tube with 0.9% NaCl solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"gc3p","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"36hvm","text":"Swab is removed from the tube and the cell suspension is centrifuged at 2000 x g for 20 mins at 4 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5if4p","text":"Supernatant is removed and the pellet is directly processed or frozen at -80 °C for processing later.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d3ij4","text":"An inoculation loop is used to collect equal amounts of pellet (∼ 2 μl) which are then dipped into a tube containing 120 μl PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cqbs1","text":"Pellets are disolved by sonicating the tube in a bath sonicator at 120 W for at least 1 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9jjqe","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cajcd","text":"Samples can be directly used for RT-QuIC assay.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"46qse","text":"Olfactory mucosa cells are extracted from the swab by vortexing the tube for 1 min at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Olfactory mucosa sampling and processing
